  "text": "Education is a well-established indicator of socio-economic status of women. Education exposes a woman to the outside world which may bring about a change in her attitude, thinking and perception about life. That change may also lead to more egalitarian and autonomous behaviour. But demographers like [CITATION_1] caution that female education could be rendered irrelevant to women's position unless it is contrasted with men's education.",
